Kartika as Kentjono Ireng

“A POWERFUL JAVANESE EARTH GODDESS”

This image garnered several awards:
1st place on International Photographic Competition’s Grand Imaging Awards, 2021
Silver Medalist on portrait category in the World Photographic Cup (WPC) 2021
Awarded the coveted Becker Memorial Award for Creative Photography, 2017.

Animation by Tahil Erickson

Notes by Designer:
KENTJONO IRENG is a primordial goddess of the Earth, mating with LINGGO GENI (the god of ocean) to produce younger gods. She is the symbol of the chaos of primordial creation. Depicted as a woman, she represents the beauty of the feminine, depicted as the glistening one.It is suggested that there are two parts to the KENTJONO IRENG mythos, the first in which KENTJONO IRENG is a creator goddess, through a “sacred marriage” between salt and fresh water from The earth, peacefully creating the cosmos through successive generations.
